Distribution of Final Probabilities — Summary & Methodology

To understand the structural shape of political prediction markets, we measure the distribution of final probabilities across all resolved markets. This shifts the focus from calibration accuracy to how markets actually allocate probability mass at resolution time.

What we are measuring

We are analyzing:

How often political markets end up at each probability level at the moment of resolution.

Specifically, we examine whether markets:

cluster at extreme certainty (0–10%, 90–100%)
occupy meaningful mass in the middle ranges
or show a smooth spread across probabilities
